name: Roostertail Creek
description:
Introduction

This canyon lies within the Uncompahgre (formally Big Blue) Wilderness area. Please practice leave-no-trace techniques to keep this canyon pristine.

Approach

From the end of CR12, hike up the Cow Creek Trail until it intersects Roostertail Creek, an unnamed creek on the maps. (Roostertail Creek was named for the impressive roostertail of water on the final rappel.)

Descent

R1: 95'
R2: 75'
R3: 85'
R4: 85'
R5: 50'
R6: 270', four tier final rappel from a tree

Exit

Return to the vehicle by streamwalking in Cow Creek. Estimate 1 mile per hour.
